name: 1inch Liquidity Protocol Deployer
description: Service proxy contract, which is accessed by the 1inch Liquidity Protocol Factory and deployed liquidation pools.

name: 1inch Liquidity Protocol Factory
description: Registry for all pools Liquidity Protocol. New pools can be created through this factory.

name: Aggregation Router V3
description: The main contract that allows you to do aggregate swaps.

name: DEX Oracle
description: The contract that finds the weighted price in ETH or in other tokens for all connected DEXs.

name: Exchange Governance
description: Module in Governance that allows to vote. Controls how much percent will go to leftover reward and how much will go to referral.

name: Fee Collector
description: Contract receives LP tokens (share tokens) and converts them into governance reward or referral rewards. The contract interacts with both the Governance and the Liquidity Protocol.

name: Governance Mothership
description: A contract-factory that allows to connect different Governance modules. Also, 1inch Stake of the token occurs through this contract.

name: Governance Rewards
description: Contract manages the 1inch Token rewards that are staked on the Governance Mothership contract.

name: Limit Order Protocol
description: Contract allows execution of offchain limit orders, and has arbitrary price discovery and conditional execution.
